==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inelegant
<hw>In*el"e*gant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inelegans</ets>: cf. F. <ets>in⟦eacute⟧l⟦eacute⟧gant</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Elegant</er>.]</ety> <def>Not elegant;
deficient in beauty, polish, refinement, grave, or ornament; wanting in
anything which correct taste requires.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What order so contrived as not to mix⟦br⟧
Tastes, not well joined, <qex>inelegant</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It renders style often obscure, always embarrassed and
<qex>inelegant</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Blair.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inelegantly</ent>⟦br⟧
